comments.text: We played a very poor game today, totally outrageous. Shout out to Joan and Balde, who gave an outstanding performance. Yes, Rayo had a poor game, full of annoying fouls and a poor field, but that was not how we were supposed to play. This better change else in the champions league, we won't even get past Quarter finals. Just a reminder, we have Chelsea, Bayern and PSG and more in our pool. comments.author: @msag6033
comments.text: In my opinion PSG's success is not only due the work that everyone at the club put in but also mainly due to Luis Campos. Smart signings, especially youth-focused talents, is the best approach. These players are as talented as any other star in the big clubs. But you need to spot them and snatch them before those big clubs go after them. There is literally no more reason to go after someone who is already big and wants the club to play for them and not the other way around. It is better to go after young talent who still have everything to prove. Kudos to the president, the coach and everyone involved in this success. Hope there is more trophies to come.
